value: Provenance: Fitzwilliam, 1792.  Manuscript note: "Cette suite du Cabinet du Roi fut donnée aux ducs de Praslin par Louis 14e et 15e.".

Part of the collection generally known as the "Cabinet du Roy" produced under the direction of Jean-Baptiste Colbert.

Comprises 38 plates from paintings by Raphael, Titian, Annibale Carracci, Palma, Guido Reni, Domenichino, Giovanni Lanfranco, Valentin de Boulogne, Veronese, Van Dyke and Poussin. Signed variously "G. Edelinck.", "Egid. Rousselet", "Steph. Picart Romanus", "Ant. Masson", "G. Chasteau", "Steph. Baudet", "G. Audran", and "G. Scotin". Most plates are undated and those that are range from 1672 to 1682. 

Pages 3-14 comprise notes in French on the first 24 plates. Text signed on p. 14 "Felibien."
Colophon on p. 14 reads "A Paris, de l'Imprimerie royale, par Sebastien Mabre-Cramoisy, directeur de ladite Imprimerie.".

Binding: red goatskin over boards, gold rolls and corner ornaments incorporating Louis XIV's monogram, gold central stamp of the arms of Louis XIV on front and back boards, gold turn-ins, gilt edges, gold spine title and royal monogram ornaments, late 17th century. Bound uniform with the remainder of the set.

[2],14p, [19] leaves of plates, [19] folded leaves of plates : ill ; 50cm
